1 ASSISTANCE IN BECOMING A RESTORATIVE PRACTICES SCHOOL IN ACCORDANCE
2 WITH § 7–306.1 OF THIS SUBTITLE; and
3 (3) Assist each county board with the implementation of the guidelines.
4 (d) (1) Subject to the provisions of subsections (b) and (c) of this section, each
5 county board shall adopt regulations designed to create and maintain within the schools
6 under its jurisdiction the atmosphere of order and discipline necessary for effective
7 learning.
8 (2) The regulations adopted by a county board under this subsection:
9 (i) Shall provide for educational and behavioral interventions,
10 restorative [approaches] PRACTICES, counseling, and student and parent conferencing;
11 (ii) Shall provide alternative programs, which may include in–school
12 suspension, suspension, expulsion, or other disciplinary measures that are deemed
13 appropriate; and
14 (iii) Shall state that the primary purpose of any disciplinary measure
15 is rehabilitative, restorative, and educational.
16 (e) (1) On or before October 1 each year, the Department shall submit to the
17 Governor and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article, the General
18 Assembly, a student discipline data report that includes a description of the uses of
19 restorative [approaches] PRACTICES in the State and a review of disciplinary practices
20 and policies in the State.
21 (2) The Department shall disaggregate the information in any student
22 discipline data report prepared by the Department by race, ethnicity, gender, disability
23 status, eligibility for free or reduced price meals or an equivalent measure of socioeconomic
24 status, English language proficiency, and type of discipline for:
25 (i) The State;
26 (ii) Each local school system; and
27 (iii) Each public school.
28 (3) Special education–related data in any report prepared under this
29 subsection shall be disaggregated by race, ethnicity, and gender.
30 (f) (1) In this subsection, “alternative school discipline practice” means a
31 discipline practice used in a public school that is not an in–school suspension or an
32 out–of–school suspension.

