7 7–306.1.
8 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
9 INDICATED.
10 (2) “RESTORATIVE PRACTICES” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN §
11 7–306 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
12 (3) “RESTORATIVE PRACTICES SCHOOL” MEANS A PUBLIC SCHOOL
13 THAT INTEGRATES RESTORATIVE PRACTICES INTO DAILY PRACTICES AND
14 ACTIVITIES OF THE WHOLE SCHOOL.
15 (B) (1) ON OR BEFORE JULY 1, 2026, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL DEVELOP
16 A COMPREHENSIVE PLAN FOR THE ESTABLISHMENT OF RESTORATIVE PRACTICES
17 SCHOOLS.
18 (2) IN DEVELOPING A COMPREHENSIVE PLAN, THE DEPARTMENT
19 SHALL CONSULT WITH AND SEEK INSIGHT FROM:
20 (I) EDUCATORS AND ADMINISTRATORS WHO HAVE
21 EFFECTIVELY ESTABLISHED AND OPERATED SCHOOLS THAT INTEGRATE
22 RESTORATIVE PRACTICES INTO THE DAILY PRACTICES AND ACTIVITIES OF THE
23 WHOLE SCHOOL; AND
24 (II) STATE AND NATIONAL ORGANIZATIONS THAT HAVE
25 STUDIED THE EFFECTIVE USE OF RESTORATIVE PRACTICES AND HAVE
26 ESTABLISHED THE MOST APPROPRIATE METHODS OF INTEGRATING RESTORATIVE
27 PRACTICES IN THE SCHOOL SETTING.
28 (C) THE COMPREHENSIVE PLAN REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF
29 THIS SECTION SHALL:
30 (1) PROVIDE A FRAMEWORK FOR LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEMS TO
31 IDENTIFY SCHOOL PERSONNEL QUALIFIED TO PROVIDE INITIAL RESTORATIVE
32 PRACTICES TRAINING AS RESTORATIVE PRACTICE COACHES TO OTHER SCHOOL
33 STAFF;

HOUSE BILL 197 5
1 (2) ESTABLISH MODEL TRAINING MATERIAL IN RESTORATIVE
2 PRACTICES FOR PERSONNEL IDENTIFIED UNDER ITEM (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION TO
3 USE IN TRAINING OTHER SCHOOL STAFF IN A MANNER THAT RESULTS IN
4 RESTORATIVE PRACTICES BEING INTEGRATED INTO SCHOOLWIDE PRACTICES AND
5 ACTIVITIES;
6 (3) ESTABLISH STANDARDS FOR WHEN A SCHOOL MAY BE
7 DESIGNATED A RESTORATIVE PRACTICES SCHOOL; AND
8 (4) DEVELOP THE INTENDED OUTCOMES AND PERFORMANCE
9 METRICS THAT THE USE OF RESTORATIVE PRACTICES ARE DESIGNED TO ACHIEVE,
10 INCLUDING IMPROVEMENTS IN THE FOLLOWING AREAS:
11 (I) STUDENT CONDUCT THAT LEADS TO DISCIPLINARY
12 ACTIONS, INCLUDING STUDENT OFFICE REFERRALS, SUSPENSIONS, EXPULSIONS,
13 AND SCHOOL ARRESTS;
14 (II) STUDENT ABSENTEEISM AND TRUANCY;
15 (III) RATES OF TEACHER TURNOVER AND ABSENTEEISM;
16 (IV) RELEVANT MENTAL HEALTH INDICATORS; AND
17 (V) SCHOOL CLIMATE INDICATORS.
18 (D) IF A COUNTY BOARD CHOOSES TO ESTABLISH A RESTORATIVE
19 PRACTICES SCHOOL WITHIN THE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM, THE COUNTY BOARD
20 SHALL USE THE COMPREHENSIVE PLAN DEVELOPED BY THE DEPARTMENT.
21 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, on or before December 1,
22 2026, the State Department of Education shall report to the Governor and, in accordance
23 with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article, the General Assembly on its comprehensive
24 plan for the establishment of Restorative Practices Schools required by § 7–306.1 of the
25 Education Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act.
26 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
27 1, 2025. Section 2 of this Act shall remain effective for a period of 2 years and, at the end of
28 June 30, 2027, Section 2 of this Act, with no further action required by the General
29 Assembly, shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.

